⚠️ CHARACTER CONSISTENCY RULES:
- Speaker A scenes: include ALL of Speaker A's Identity + Costume + LoRA tags
- Speaker B scenes: include ALL of Speaker B's Identity + Costume + LoRA tags
- NEVER mix character tags between speakers
- Do NOT invent, modify, or omit any character appearance tags
- Do NOT add alternative hair colors, eye colors, hair lengths, skin colors, or outfits
- NEVER add tags like brown_hair when Identity Tags say red_hair, or brown_eyes when Identity Tags say blue_eyes
- Use ONLY the exact Identity/Costume tags provided above — do not paraphrase or substitute
- Place character tags BEFORE expression/pose/environment tags in image_prompt

⚠️ DIALOGUE STRUCTURE RULES:
- STRICT: Create {{ ((duration / 2.5) | round | int) }}-{{ ((duration / 2) | round | int) }} scenes for {{ duration }} seconds total
- NEVER exceed {{ ((duration / 2) | round | int) }} scenes. Fewer scenes is acceptable.
- Speaker A gets roughly half the scenes, Speaker B gets the rest
- Alternate speakers: A → B → A → B → A...
- Most scenes show ONLY the speaking character (single person in frame)
- Both characters share the SAME environment/location across all scenes
- Conversation must feel natural and flow logically
